## Repo context

- App id: `com.u2re.ioclient`
- Android workflows live in `package.json` scripts:
  - `npm run android:devices` (show adb devices)
  - `npm run android:log` (logcat filter)
  - `npm run android:adb:reset` (adb restart)

## When you need ADB wireless debugging

Ask the user to do **Android → Developer options → Wireless debugging**:

- For pairing: "Pair device with pairing code"
  - Then on Windows run: `pwsh -NoProfile -File .\vbc-pack\windows\vbc-adb-pair.ps1`
- For connecting: use the "IP address & port"
  - Then on Windows run: `pwsh -NoProfile -File .\vbc-pack\windows\vbc-adb-connect.ps1`

If the user pastes an `ip:port`, you can also tell them to copy it to clipboard and run the connect script (it auto-detects clipboard).

## When you need logs for debugging

Prefer these first:

- `npm run android:log` (or VSCode task: `Android: Logcat (Android runtime)`)
- `npm run android:adb:reset` if devices show offline

If the user is on-phone (Termux), ask them to run:

- `vbc-pack/termux/vbc-ai-prompt.sh`

Then paste the clipboard output into the chat.

## If you need a QR to transfer short text to the phone

On Windows you can generate a QR image (requires Python + `qrcode[pil]`):

- `pwsh -NoProfile -File .\vbc-pack\windows\vbc-make-qr.ps1 -Text "adb://192.168.1.50:39345"`

The phone can "Open with Termux" if `~/.termux/termux-url-opener` is installed from `vbc-pack/termux/termux-url-opener`.

